Mitra's Paladins are Her holy and devout warriors. Her last line
of defense against the evils that serve Her arch-nemesis Set.
They take a more active role in the forms of spreading Mitra's 
word and ridding the world of evil influences.

The Paladin guild provides a means to play in a more combat oriented 
guild than the somewhat passive Clerics.  However, the road to 
being Mitra's ultimate warrior is not an easy one. You will be 
required to demonstrate your skills in a wide variety of areas.
These areas include knowledge of all types of weapons and combat
techniques, horsemanship, and reputation. For the Paladin able to
meet all of the requirements to finally advance to Lord Paladin, the
rewards will be well worth the effort.

Paladins rise through righteous battle: worthy kills earn Paladin XP
and guild levels advance automatically -- read 'palhelp advancement'
for the details.
